{"code":"# Given densities from the LibreText's Introductory Chemistry materials
# Density of honey at 25¬∞C: 1.42 g/cm¬≥
# Density of mayonnaise at 25¬∞C: 0.94 g/cm¬≥

# Constants
DENSITY_HONEY = 1.42  # g/cm¬≥
DENSITY_MAYONNAISE = 0.94  # g/cm¬≥

# Conversion factors
GALLON_TO_CUP = 16  # 1 gallon = 16 cups
CUP_TO_CM3 = 236.588  # 1 cup = 236.588 cm¬≥

# Calculate the mass of 1 gallon of honey
volume_honey_cm3 = GALLON_TO_CUP * CUP_TO_CM3
mass_honey_g = volume_honey_cm3 * DENSITY_HONEY

volume_mayonnaise_cm3 = GALLON_TO_CUP * CUP_TO_CM3

# Calculate the number of cups to remove from honey to weigh less than mayonnaise
cups_removed = 0
while mass_honey_g >= mass_mayonnaise_g:
    mass_honey_g -= mass_one_cup_honey_g
    cups_removed += 1

cups_removed"}

{"code":"# Given densities from the LibreTexts Chemistry materials
# Density of honey at 25¬∞C: 1.42 g/cm¬≥
# Density of mayonnaise at 25¬∞C: 0.94 g/cm¬≥

# Convert densities to g/mL (1 cm¬≥ = 1 mL)
density_honey = 1.42  # g/mL
density_mayonnaise = 0.94  # g/mL

# Volume of a gallon in mL
volume_gallon_mL = 3785.41  # 1 gallon = 3785.41 mL

# Calculate the mass of a gallon of honey and mayonnaise
mass_honey = density_honey * volume_gallon_mL
mass_mayonnaise = density_mayonnaise * volume_gallon_mL

# Volume of a cup in mL
volume_cup_mL = 240  # 1 cup = 240 mL

# Calculate the mass of honey removed per cup
mass_honey_per_cup = density_honey * volume_cup_mL

# Calculate the number of cups to remove for honey to weigh less than mayonnaise
cups_removed = 0
current_mass_honey = mass_honey

while current_mass_honey >= mass_mayonnaise:
    current_mass_honey -= mass_honey_per_cup
    cups_removed += 1

cups_removed"}
